osx-trash is a command line program to manipulate the trash on Mac OS X. It
uses AppleScript via Scripting Bridge to manipulate the trash, just like the
Finder does.  Here's a simple example:

  % touch foo bar baz
  % trash -l
  % trash foo ba*
  % trash -l
  /Users/dave/.Trash/foo
  /Users/dave/.Trash/bar
  /Users/dave/.Trash/baz
  % trash -e
  % trash -l

Using AppleScript has a number of benefits.  First, it creates unique names when trashed:

  % touch foo
  % trash foo
  % touch foo
  % trash foo
  % trash -l
  /Users/dave/.Trash/foo
  /Users/dave/.Trash/foo 20-38-20

It also handles trashes on different disks properly:

  % touch foo
  % trash foo
  % touch /Volumes/DiskImage/bar
  % trash /Volumes/DiskImage/bar
  % trash -l
  /Users/dave/.Trash/foo
  /Volumes/DiskImage/.Trashes/501/bar

